title: Grateful Dead Live at Musikhalle on 1972-04-29
description:
Set 1

Playin' In The Band, Sugaree, Mr. Charlie, Black Throated Wind, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Big Boss Man, Jack Straw, Loser, Chinatown Shuffle, Me & My Uncle, Big Railroad Blues, Good Lovin', Casey Jones

Set 2

Greatest Story Ever Told, He's Gone, Next Time You See Me, Dark Star-> Sugar Magnolia-> Caution (Do Not Stop on Tracks)-> Who Do You Love, E: One More Saturday Night, E: Uncle John's Band*

Second Encore

reviews.review_text:
A Work of Beauty Well done.
This is a well-played show & it has great sound.  Crank it Up & enjoy...,
Nice chunk of the Europe 72 experience Very nice mix and the band is on. Just listened through once & there's a lot here. I'd recommend to anyone who digs this tour.
Best 1972 matrix on IA Wow. Five stars on every level.  Garcia's tone is just amazing here with the addition of the audience source: sounds the way that mercury looks and behaves.

In a word Beautiful.

Another chance to get a free version of this show, as well as the recent Miller upgrade, if you don't have the E72 Trunk (I do, possibly the only one in the UK). This version of the show is professionally done i.e. commercial release quality, albeit without the packaging (tho' the Trader's Vault front cover is nice). I took a FLAC copy from Lossless Legs, using TLH to produce an mp3 (@320 kbps) version (with gaps between the tracks) for my mp3 player and a WAV version (without the gaps) for burning to CD for the car and the big stereo in the living room.

You probably already know the show and the wonderful transition between "Dark Star" and "Sugar Magnolia". "Mr. Charlie" is a good example of the excellent mix - you can hear both Pigpen's organ on the left channel and Keith's piano on the right quite clearly.

My E72 trunk ? Well, the actual CDs remain unplayed (I hope none of them are faulty!), ensuring none of the covers get damaged. I grabbed a FLAC version from 'Yo-ho-ho and a bottle of rum.com' (think Pirate) which I have been listening to on a day-to-day basis as above. Will probably have the trunk placed in my coffin to accompany me during my travel to the afterlife when that day finally arrives !

Back to Dusborne's work - EXCELLENT.

TW 4-10-0-9

Quality Great Europe 72 show ,with great mtx sound..About as near to the fabled box set as this UK Deadhead will probably get..Typical Europe set(great!) Extremely tight playing from all involved..Special respect to Billy for just bein there like a workhorse at every show layin the beat down(sans Mickey)..Pigpens very prominent at this show too with 5 pig tunes to enjoy..Wunderbah!!!
Europe 72' This is a exceptional show from the Europe 72' era.Pig is awesome and Jerry is in fine form.5 golden stars
Underrated show I  mean, all the trappings of a Europe 72 show, but then Dark Star>Sugar Magnolia>Caution, about an hours worth?
